annotation.TEXT: Alright, now that I'm over here with the two keys, I'm hoping that by throwing them so that they land near the wall, that I can somehow get squeezed through the floor while flying and holding the P-switch.
To be continued...
I find it hilarious how the fish just shoot off the screen like that!
Alright, a change in scenery. It's about time.
Alright, this next area is all underwater, and you can get a free cape feather right near the entrance!
Test annotation, lower-right.
Now, you may be wondering, "Where are all the Yoshi coins in this level?"
For this Rex, you probably want to get up there and stomp it ASAP.
And now for "the maze", just like in the original game, except it's underwater.
MOON!!!
Wait, did the P-switch reveal anything special over here?
Also, just like Yelloh heaven zone, this is an easy way to get a blue Yoshi, and this one doesn't involve any glitches whatsoever (which is unusual for this game)!
Okay, the door should appear right where the keyhole is. Here goes...
Only 30? I should've been able to get at least 40 there. Still, that's exactly enough for a bonus game!
Here's a good place to use that trick.
Looks like I'll be replaying this level...
Nuts. I guess there's nothing there. Although, I'm in a good position to leap at the goal tape now.
Demo count: 19
Test annotation, upper-left.
Oh, yeah. I gotta say "MOOOONNN"!!! Also, I'm going to need to take both keys with me to the left, so let's double-grab them while in flight!
Well, this fish seems to be anchored in reality, but not for long!
MOON!!!
And I think the other 1 hour ago to the right despawned off the side of the screen, leaving me just the buzzy down here to deal with.
Don't let yourself get trapped by this Rex while going for that one coin in the tiny alcove! (You're not that stupid, right?)
Then, hit the ? blocks to find two more feathers and wings! If you have Yoshi, you can clear the level now, but I don't, so I'm going to have to play out the rest of the level.
The Magic Banzais should all just fly harmlessly over your head while you're standing still, so don't worry about them hitting you.
Okay, here's my plan: Stand perfectly still on the stable edges of the platforms while invisible.
Aha, I knew I could fry and collect the coin of at least one of those fish!

Hello, and welcome back to Chaos CompleXX! I'm back here yet again, and this time, I'm going to get that P-switch from the left side of this area over to the right side! (Note: This is tool-assisted, of course.)
Hey there, cheep-cheep! How's it... going?
Alright, let's start off by spin jumping on this buzzy, and... Hmm... How do I get onto that high yellow platform?
WHOA!!! Hey, I'm not dead?
Hopefully you won't be in the middle of a jump just as a Magic Banzai appears.
Well, that 1 hour ago is now past tense.
There's a 1 hour ago below this power up block you can trash, but watch out for the disco 1 hour ago that'll be coming at you from the upper-right.
Not like that! Who wants pancakes?
Well, they're all right here! However, let's read the message box first.
Alright, now I'm completely done with that level (assuming there's no secret exit that I'm unaware of). Next time, I'll take on the "House in Yalley"!

Just placing some test annotations here, as lately, the annotations have not been showing up properly when I watch the video on the video page. They're often way to the left of where I placed them in the annotation editor, and sometimes with the text spilling out of the bottom of their boxes. Is anyone else seeing such glitches?
Yeah, I know when, but what was the name?
Not that I can see. Well, that sucks. I'm outta here.
Now, in the original game, there were two places where you could get checkpoint 1-ups in Valley of Bowser 2's "maze", but I have no idea if any checkpoint 1-ups are here. Do you guys know of any?
Nuts, failed to block clone with this 1 hour ago shell.
And I couldn't even suck consistently enough to get all mushrooms around the edges.
There's not enough time to both grab this Yoshi coin and get over the next structure in one shot, so you'll have to be patient here.
...after I go get a Yoshi, that is!
You can kill this fish just for the heck of it if you want, but there's no hidden feather block offscreen here like in the original game, I don't think (not that you'd need it).
NUUUTS!!! I guess that door had been removed. What a bummer...

Grab the Yoshi coin quickly while the land is up, but then don't rush towards midpoint. Wait until the land falls and rises again before going for midpoint. (You can grab this mushroom while you wait.)
Oh, it's an autoscrolling level, with purple coins, lava, and non-harmful spikes made out of steep slopes.
Whoa, that was a fast drop! Yeah, whenever you step off of a layer 2 ledge, you suddenly fall fast for some reason, even if you're underwater.
Demo count: 18
...you can slip through the moving floor! This can make many parts of this area easier and faster!
Okay, I've definitely got enough time for another level. This one is "GOING DOWN AND UP pawprint". Let's-a-go!
If you eat the disco 1 hour ago shell here, you can fly, which might be helpful in avoiding the "bottomless pit clause" in these wells.
Thwack!
Okay, the land shifted suddenly here, so that means it's gonna drop... right?
Oh, yeah. The one in the upper-left is on the subscreen boundary, so you can easily rack up a ton of lives here if you need to! Just don't touch the upper half of the coin until you're done.
Whoa, close call there. Yeah, having to swim makes this trickier, since you can't run full speed.
...Oookay, then. Now, there is a neat trick you can do here. As the land is rising, if you hold down and continuously paddle...
Yep, this level definitely going harder now, with all that invisibility magic being used early on!
Awesome, my plan worked!
There are four Yoshi coins here, bringing the total number of possible Yoshi coins in this level up to seven.
Well, seeing as how there are some remnants of the original level still here, I'm hoping to do the same thing now!
...WHAT THE?!
Back to the spike platforms. Now, that may look like a Torpedo Ted launcher below, but it's non-functional, so don't worry.
Now, I'm a little suspicious of whether there's a secret to the upper-left, and it looks like there's just enough space to build up running speed here...
When they leave the screen, Yoshi reappears. You definitely want to have Yoshi during this area, though. Otherwise, Mario will be the one to become invisible!
Now, let's collect the eight Yoshi coins!
Am I crazy enough to try challenging that level again without going to get a Yoshi first? Yes I am!
Test annotation, upper-right.
Alright, made it to the end of this area!
Also, there are Banzai Bills, which have some sort of magic ability here, which makes Yoshi invisible whenever they appear.
Gulp!
Be careful here. Don't let a Rex corner you. Use the opening to stomp or jump over it. (Or fry, cape spin, or eat the Rex if you have those abilities.)
Oh, and under no circumstances should you stand under the small floating yellow ledge when it appears! Just don't!

Now, I could get the wings right now, and be able to reach five Yoshi coins in the bonus area, but I want to maximize my profits, so I'm going to go claim the two from the "maze" as well. (Leave Yoshi outside of the "maze" if you do this.)
Test annotation, upper-center, below the reserve item box.
And now for the wings bonus area, which is different from the previous three, but still identical to one of the original SMW's.
However, there are certain places, like here, where you'll have to go over a tall wall, so the trick really isn't all that useful for these.
I guess that piece of land was high enough that the "bottomless pit clause" didn't trigger. Still, I highly recommend trying to avoid being in these wells when they plummet.
Alright, it's time for the level you've all been waiting for...
If you have a cape, you can glide under that bone and land inside of this landmass, but there's nothing special there. (If you do that, you can exit the landmass by jumping to the right.)
Well, I must not have been paying attention when you told me then. Could you tell me again? ...Oh, forget it...
Even worse, now I'm vulnerable to the invisibility spell!
This Rex looks trapped, but be careful. It can still bite if you don't approach it right! Also, watch out for another non-magical Banzai fly by here.

If you happen to be turned invisible during a jump, just assume you'll make the jump and continue holding the horizontal direction towards the steep slope that you landed near until you reappear. That should still keep you from falling into the lava.
Now, remember how in the original SMW's version of this level, you would access the normal exit by going through a P-switch door surrounded by a coin outline?
Alright, I guess that level's done. But, I only got three Yoshi coins, and I know this level has more than that!
Oh, yeah. I kind of want to get that power up...
Okay, what was it?
Just let the Magic Banzai Bill fly off the screen, then resume moving when you reappear.
Wait patiently until the yellow platforms fall, then step onto them.
Ooh, I just passed a million points! Sweet!
And, it dumps me right at the goal. Note: The purple "lava" to the left is safe to touch.
(Yeah, the remaining Yoshi coins are in the wings bonus area, in case you hadn't figured that out already.)
I just told you: "1 hour ago".
Oh, no! Where'd I go?
...3-1! Hmm... "BABZAIS YALLEY"? What's that mean? Must be some sort of foreign name. Well, let's enter it!
Watch out for that 1 hour ago and make absolutely sure you're not in one of those wells when they come crashing down! Otherwise, you will die as if you fell into a bottomless pit.
And, right off the bat, I suck.
I'm guessing I landed in the lava over here...
Demo count: 20
I will definitely do better than that next time, or else my name is Mud!
...Maybe not...?
Oh, by the way, the naming vote had a clear winner this time: "1 hour ago".
Of course, when the land falls back down, you'll be forced back into the opening, but you can just repeat the trick as the land is rising again.
Huh. I didn't turn invisible this time. I guess that Banzai isn't magical. That's good.
It was "1 hour ago".
Test annotation, lower-left.
That was a nice time saver.
Yeah, be careful if you backtrack in this area (or just when you're moving in general). The yellow land can shift oddly in certain spots, which could cause you to fall through the floor.
Okay let's not be a stupid moron this time!
Oh, crap! NO, YOSHI!!! Man, that was a bad jump on my part...
